{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493131","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493131"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:57:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:57:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1234"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1234","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1234"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.04,0.07,0.56,0.32]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1234"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97669"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1234","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1234"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1234"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80270"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"675"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"1356"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"4640"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5820"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1545"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1585"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33513"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34926"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/97669"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old man presents with painless lesions on his palms that have been present for about one week. He does not have involvement over his lips/mouth. He reports a two week history of feeling generally tired and fatigued with subjective fevers and myalgia but thought he \u0022just had the flu\u0022 until these lesions appeared. He has no significant medical history and rarely visits the doctor. He is single and has a number of sexual partners. He reports that he works in business and travels frequently for work. The physical examination is unremarkable apart from changes on the palms (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Eczema","Pityriasis rosea","Hand-foot-mouth disease","Secondary syphilis","Erythema multiforme major"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESyphilis is a sexually transmitted\u00a0infection\u00a0caused by the spirochete\u00a0\u003Cem\u003ETreponema pallidum\u003C/em\u003E. There has been an increase in cases of syphilis in recent years. Syphilis infection has multiple stages including primary syphilis (characterised by genital chancre), secondary syphilis and tertiary syphilis. Secondary syphilis is characterised by systemic symptoms including fever, malaise, myalgia and arthralgia as well as a cutaneous rash (1). The rash associated with \u003Cstrong\u003Esecondary syphilis\u003C/strong\u003E can take various forms but characteristically appears on the soles of the feet and the palms of the hands, referred to as \u0027copper pennies\u0027. The manifestations of secondary syphilis occur some four to ten weeks after the primary infection. The rash may last several weeks. The rash is not consistent with any form of eczema. The rash associated with pityriasis rosea will more likely occur on the chest and back. Hand, foot and mouth disease presents with vesicopustular eruptions on the acral skin. Erythema multiforme major can have very much the same presentation, except it tends to be more widespread than involvement over the palms only and would often have mucosal involvement.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The incidence of syphilis in Australia is increasing, particularly in young Indigenous peoples."],"references":["Dermnet NZ [Internet]. 2003 [updated 2020 Jan; cited 2020 Feb 11]. Available from: https://dermnetnz.org/topics/syphilis/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80270"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1234"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18467"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18467","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18467"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5e5e496e-b637-406e-bcf1-5928550741db.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5e5e496e-b637-406e-bcf1-5928550741db.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":600,"height":411}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/80270"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-08T16:46:47+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-08T16:48:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1234"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97669"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14